  "text": "Mendoza et al. studied the inconsistencies in input validation logic between apps and their respective web API services [CITATION_1] . They developed a tool to extract requests to web API services from an app, and to infer sample input values that violate the implemented constraints found in the app, such as email address or JSON content validation executed on the client side. They then analyzed app-violating request logic on the server side via black box testing. From a set of 10 000 popular Android apps, they found 4 000 apps that do not properly implement input validation for web API services. Investigation of web API hijacking vulnerabilities in 1 000 apps showed that the security and privacy of millions of users are at risk.",
